---
# ============================================================================
# CO-LOCATION PATTERN (recommended for all new blogs)
# ============================================================================
# Save this file at:
#   content/blog/<your-slug>/index.mdx
#
# Then put all images for this blog in the SAME folder:
#   content/blog/<your-slug>/hero.webp
#   content/blog/<your-slug>/diagram-1.webp
#   content/blog/<your-slug>/screenshot.png
#
# Run `npm run dev` and the sync script will automatically copy your images
# into /public/blog/<slug>/ so Next.js can serve them.
#
# In FRONTMATTER below, image paths can be:
#   - Just the filename:  featuredImage: "hero.webp"
#       → auto-resolves to /blog/<slug>/hero.webp
#   - Absolute path:      featuredImage: "/blog/<slug>/hero.webp"
#   - External URL:       featuredImage: "https://..."
#
# In MDX BODY below, always use absolute paths:
#   ![alt](/blog/<slug>/diagram-1.webp)
# ============================================================================

title: "Your Blog Title Here"
metaTitle: "Shorter SEO Title for Browser Tab"
description: "Write a 150-160 character meta description for SEO. This appears in Google search results."
category: "Marketing"
# Lowercase strings. Falls back to [lowercased category] if omitted.
tags: ["marketing strategy", "lead generation"]
publishedDate: "2026-05-28"
# Optional — defaults to publishedDate. Bump when refreshing content.
updatedAt: "2026-05-28"

# Just the filename — auto-resolves to /blog/<slug>/hero.webp at runtime.
# The image file itself lives at content/blog/<slug>/hero.webp.
featuredImage: "hero.webp"
featuredImageAlt: "Descriptive alt text for the featured image"
ogImage: "hero.webp"

# Optional overrides — default to Rafael Hernandez / CEO and Co-Founder of Great Marketing AI.
# author: "Rafael Hernandez"
# authorRole: "CEO and Co-Founder of Great Marketing AI"

keyTakeaways:
  - "First key takeaway here"
  - "Second key takeaway"
  - "Third key takeaway"

faqs:
  - q: "First FAQ question?"
    a: "Answer to the first FAQ. Can be a long paragraph."
  - q: "Second FAQ question?"
    a: "Answer to the second FAQ."

# Set to true to hide the post in production (still visible in dev for review).
# draft: true
---

## First H2 Heading

Your content here. Use H2s (`##`) for main sections — these show up in the
sidebar TOC. Use H3s (`###`) for subsections — these appear under their parent
H2 when the reader expands the TOC dropdown.

Inline images use ABSOLUTE paths like this:

![Alt text describing this diagram](/blog/your-slug-here/diagram-1.webp)

Replace `your-slug-here` with your actual blog slug (which matches the folder
name).

### A Subsection (H3)

This will appear nested under "First H2 Heading" in the sidebar TOC.

## Second H2 Heading

More content here.
